==Days of Week (Hafte ke Din ہفتہ کے دن )==
{| border="1" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="1" !bgcolor=#EEEEEE|Din !bgcolor=#EEEEEE|Day !bgcolor=#EEEEEE|In Urdu Script |- |Piir |Monday | پير |- |Mangal |Tuesday |منگل |- |Budh |Wednesday |بدھ |- |Jume'raat |Thursday |جمعرات |- |Juma'h |Friday |جمعـء |- |Haftah / Sanichar |Saturday |ہفتہ / سنیچر |- |Itwaar |Sunday |اتوار |- |}
{| border="1" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="1" !bgcolor=#EEEEEE|English !bgcolor=#EEEEEE|Urdu Script !bgcolor=#EEEEEE|Transliteration |- |Today||آج ||āj |- |Yesterday/Tomorrow (depends on context/tense)||کل||kal |- |Day after tomorrow||پرسوں||parso<sup>n</sup> |- |Day after day after tomorrow, the third day past today||ترسون||tarso<sup>n</sup> |- |Week||ہفتہ||hafta |- |This week||اس ہفتے||is hafteh |- |Month||مہینہ||mahīnah |- |}
[[Category:Urdu]]

Interrogatives are normally used to ask questions. Sometimes they may refer to a whole sentence or situation.
{| border="1" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="1" !bgcolor=#EEEEEE|English !bgcolor=#EEEEEE|Urdu !bgcolor=#EEEEEE|Transliteration |- |how/of what kind?||<big>کَیسا، کَیسی، کَیسے، کس ترح</big>||kaisā, kaisī, kaise, kis tarah? |- |how much/many?||<big>کتنا، کتنی، کتنے</big>||kitnā, kitnī, kitne? |- |what? (also used at the beginning of yes/no questions)||<big>کیا</big>||kyā? |- |when?||<big>کب، کس وقت</big>||kab, kis waqt? |- |where?||<big>کہاں، کدھر</big>||kahā<sup>n</sup>, kidhar? |- |who?||<big>کَون</big>||kaun? |- |which?||<big>کَون سا</big>||kaunsa? |- |why?||<big>کیوں</big>||kyū<sup>n</sup>? |- |}
